condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :5.01 (a) | Description :MWE (on behalf of the relevant secondary cities) and AAWSA have each adopted the revisedProject Implementation Manual, in form andsubstance satisfactory to the association. | Due Date :30-Sep-2012

Finance Agreement :5.01 (a) | Description :MWR, on behalf of the secondary cities, and AAWSA have adopted the ProjectImplementation Manual in form and substance satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :13-Sep-2007

Finance Agreement :5.01 (b) | Description :AAWSA has recruited (or assigned) a procurement specialist for the project; and (ii) thePCU has recruited (or assigned) for the secondary city of DireDawa, a procurement specialist and a project coordinator withtechnical background, each having terms of reference, qualifications and experience acceptable to the association. | Due Date:30-Sep-2012

Finance Agreement :5.01 (c) | Description :MoFED and AAWSA have entered into a Subsidiary Agreement for the purpose of execution ofpart A of the project, in form and substance satisfactory to IDA | Due Date :13-Sep-2007

Finance Agreement :5.01 (c) | Description :MoFED has entered into the Subsidiary agreement with AAWSA to make a portion of proceedsof Financing available for the execution of Part A of the project, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | DueDate :30-Sep-2012

Finance Agreement :IV. B (b) of Schedule 2 | Description :No withdrawal shall be made for payments made prior to the date of thisAgreement with respect to amount of the Additional Credit, except that withdrawals of the proceeds of the Additional credit up toan aggregate amount not to exceed ten million ($10,000,000) equivalent may be made for payments made prior to this date but on orafter December 1, 2011, for Eligible Expenditures. | Due Date :30-Sep-2013

Finance Agreement :VI. (c) of Schedule 2 | Description :The Recipient (through MWE) shall cause the Dire Dawa water Utility torecruit an internal auditor, having terms of reference, qualifications and experience acceptable to the association. | Due Date:31-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :VI. (d) of Schedule 2 | Description :The Recipient (through MWE) shall cause the Dire Dawa water Utility toassign, no later than two (2) months after the effective Date, a focal person for financial management for the project, havingterms of reference, qualifications and experience acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :30-Nov-2012

Finance Agreement :VI. 1 (a) of Schedule 2 | Description :The Recipient (through MWE) shall cause the Dire Dawa water Utility tohave its financial statement (which reflect operations, resources and expenditures of such utility as a whole) for fiscal year2009/10 and 2010/2011 audited and remitted to the Association, in form and substance acceptable to the Association. | Due Date:31-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :VI. 2 of Schedule 2 | Description :The recipient shall cause AAWSA to recruit (or assign), no later than six (6)months after the Effective Date, a contract management specialist, having terms of reference, qualifications and experienceacceptable to the Association. | Due Date :31-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :VI.1 (b) of Schedule 2 | Description :The Recipient (through MWE) shall cause the Dire Dawa water Utility toprepare and adopt a financial and accounting manual which sets out its overall financial and accounting processes and procedures,in form and substance acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :31-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement:5.01 (b) | Description :MWR has employed a PCU Project Coordinator, a procurement specialist, and an additionalaccountant, all having experience and qualifications satisfactory to the association. | Due Date :13-Sep-2007
